Tchekhovskoy et al. (2010) confirmed the work of Komissarov et al. (2009) by also exploring the effect of a finite stellar envelope on the structure of axisymmetric collapsar jets. They treated the jet-envelope interface as a collimating rigid wall, which opens up at the stellar surface to mimic loss of collimation. The onset of deconfinement causes a burst of acceleration accompanied by a slight increase in the opening angle. The results \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
