Schneider et al. (1993) proposed to use the method of Harten, Lax and van Leer (HLL hereafter Harten et al., 1983) to integrate the equations of RHD. This method avoids the explicit calculation of the eigenvalues and eigenvectors of the Jacobian matrices and is based on an approximate solution of the original Riemann problems with a single intermediate state 30\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
