In their discussion, Mignone and Bodo (2006) differentiated between the cases where the component of the magnetic field normal to the contact discontinuity, Bx, vanishes and where it does not. In either case, the speed of the contact discontinuity is assumed to be equal to the (constant) normal velocity in the intermediate states, i.e., \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
