				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${{dp} \over {d{Z^{\prime}}}} = {\left. {{{\partial p} \over {\partial \chi }}} \right\vert_\rho }{{d\chi } \over {d{Z^{\prime}}}} + {\left. {{{\partial p} \over {\partial \rho }}} \right\vert_\chi }{{d\rho } \over {d{Z^{\prime}}}}.$$\end{document} Mignone and McKinney provided explicit expressions of the thermodynamic derivatives ∂p/∂χ∣ρ and ∂p/∂ρ∣χ that avoid catastrophic cancellation in the non-relativistic limit (χ/ρ,p/ρ → 0) for the approximate Synge EOS (Mathews, 1971; Mignone et al., 2005b; Ryu et al., 2006). The authors claim that their inversion method is accurate in the ultrarelativistic limit as long as \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
